section.section:
Any land along or near any State highway may be acquired under this subtitle:
To protect the highway or any scenery along or near it;
For landscaping the highway;
To provide parking and service areas along the highway; or
For any similar purpose.

text.section:
The interests in land that may be acquired under this section include easements restricting or subjecting to administrative regulation the right of the owner or other persons to:
Erect buildings or other structures;
Construct a private drive or road;
Remove or destroy shrubbery or trees;
Place trash or unsightly or offensive material on the land; or
Display signs, billboards, or advertisements on the land.
